      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "ASTRO WORLD (6) returns for the G & A Williams camp and is a noted fresh performer. She was a barnstorming winner over this trip in this grade when resuming at Ascot back in October. The form around her stacks up everywhere and she keeps Pike from her lead-up trial. Looks the one to beat in the last. Stablemate THINK PINK DAZE (7) took a nice step forward second-up when finishing full of running to just miss. Peaking now and is drawn much kinder. Can knock off the stablemate.  HOUSEWIFE (1) was good second-up and is open to further improvement, kept fresh with 33 days in-between. Should be blending in nicely at the top of the straight and can give this a big shake. PONY UP (2) went close to making it two on the trot at the latest in a blanket finish. Claimer stays on to get in well at the weights but the drop in trip looks an interesting move. Keeping safe. MISS VALMALENCO (5) will be rock-hard fit now following a nice effort at Ascot last start when fourth.",
